10 adding a new section to read:
11 "§ 163-41.3. Suspension or removal of precinct officials; vacancies."
12 SECTION 2.2.(b) G.S. 163-41(d) is recodified as G.S. 163-41.3.
13 SECTION 2.2.(c) G.S. 163-41, as amended by this section, reads as rewritten:
14 "§ 163-41. Precinct chief judges and judges of election; appointment; terms of office;
15 qualifications; vacancies; oaths of office.
16 (a) Appointment of Chief Judge and Judges. – At the meeting required by G.S. 163-31 to
17 be held on the Tuesday following the third Monday in August of the year in which they are
18 appointed, the county board of elections shall appoint one person to act as chief judge and two
19 other persons to act as judges of election for each precinct in the county. Their terms of office
20 shall continue for two years from the specified date of appointment and until their successors are
21 appointed and qualified, except that if a nonresident of the precinct is appointed as chief judge
22 or judge for a precinct, that person's term of office shall end if the county board of elections
23 appoints a qualified resident of the precinct of the same party to replace the nonresident chief
24 judge or judge. It shall be their the duty of the precinct officials to conduct the primaries and
25 elections within their respective precincts. Persons appointed to these offices must be registered
